-- Suzlon Hits Roadblock Selling Parts of Repower Unit, Handelsblatt Reports
-- Eva von Schaper
-- 2010-09-07T06:18:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-07/suzlon-having-trouble-selling-parts-of-repower-unit-handelsblatt-reports.html

          
          
             Suzlon Energy Ltd. is having
problems selling part of its Repower AG unit,  Handelsblatt 
reported, citing unidentified people in the industry.  
 Suzlon is said to have priced a 25 percent stake in its
Repower Systems AG unit at about 500 million euros ($640
million), the newspaper said. The stock market currently values
Repower at about 1 billion euros, the newspaper said.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
